# AI-DLC Workflow

This project uses the AI-DLC methodology (plugin `ai-dlc@ai-dlc`, enabled in `.claude/settings.local.json`). Cursor and Claude Code share the same state under `.ai-dlc/` so work is resumable and cross-agent.

## When to engage AI-DLC

- **Engage**: features, refactors, investigations, anything that touches >1 file or has non-obvious trade-offs.
- **Skip**: typo fixes, one-line tweaks, direct questions about the code.

For small tasks, just work directly. For everything else, use the flow below.

## The flow

### 1. Elaborate (once per intent)

Run `/ai-dlc:elaborate` (Claude Code) or follow the same structure manually in Cursor. Produces under `.ai-dlc/{slug}/`:

- `intent.md` — what we're building and why.
- `completion-criteria.md` — atomic, measurable, verifiable criteria.
- `discovery.md` — domain findings that inform the build.

Criteria must be specific ("Users can log in with Google OAuth", "API p95 < 200ms"), not vague ("make it work").

### 2. Execute through hats (one Bolt = one pass)

Default workflow: `planner → builder → reviewer`.

| Hat | Focus | Writes |
|---|---|---|
| Planner | Plan this iteration | `current-plan.md` |
| Builder | Implement to spec | code + `scratchpad.md` |
| Reviewer | Verify vs. criteria | approve → Bolt done; reject → back to planner |

- **Advance** when the current hat's deliverable is complete.
- **Fail fast** — reviewer rejection returns to the previous hat immediately.
- Don't skip hats. Don't linger.
- Reviewer rejection doesn't reset work; it starts a new Bolt on the same unit.

### 3. Persist state as you go

Write into `.ai-dlc/{slug}/state/`:

- `iteration.json` — current hat, Bolt count, status.
- `current-plan.md` — living plan for the active iteration.
- `scratchpad.md` — learnings, gotchas, partial results.
- `blockers.md` — explicit blockers so the next Bolt can unblock.

Save early, save often. `/clear` is cheap when state is on disk.

## Configuration

`.ai-dlc/settings.yml` holds project-level defaults (VCS, default branch, change strategy, passes, review agents). Resolution order when reading config:

1. Unit frontmatter (highest)
2. Intent settings (`.ai-dlc/{slug}/settings.yml`)
3. Global settings (`.ai-dlc/settings.yml`) (lowest)

## Anti-patterns

- Starting to code before elaborating.
- Vague completion criteria.
- Fighting the context reset instead of leaning on files.
- Silent blockers — document them in `blockers.md`.
- Running the same workflow in Cursor with a different state store. Both agents use `.ai-dlc/`.

## Hand-off with Engram

When an intent completes, save an Engram observation (see `engram-memory.mdc`) summarizing the outcome and linking the intent slug. AI-DLC state is per-intent; Engram is cross-intent memory.
